frus:attachment.p:
In light of the paper on which comment is being made and of the views of the Joint Chiefs of Staff reproduced above, consideration has been given to the alternative United States courses of action set forth at the end of that paper. Briefly, these courses are:
a.
Increase United States aid to the maximum extent feasible;
b.
Withdraw United States aid;
c.
Continue United States aid on the basis of programs now authorized;
d.
Shift United States recognition and aid from the National Government of China to appropriate regional regimes that may arise as a result of the collapse of the present National Government.
